# version file — generated by hatch's uv-dynamic-versioning hook from git
# state. Different on every commit; keep ignored.
src/hc_portal/_version.py

# `_metadata.py` is generated by the apx build hook from [tool.apx.metadata]
# in pyproject.toml. Its content is static (only changes if pyproject does)
# and the BFF imports it deeply (`backend/core/_factory.py`, `_static.py`,
# etc.), so a fresh checkout (CI without `apx build`) would crash on
# import. We commit the file rather than gate every callsite on a try/except
# or front-load `apx build` in CI just to regenerate a 7-line static config.

